@uCrunch here's some stuff i found years ago

you can simplify a lot of this to just knowing that platforms benefit you a lot https://t.co/HZT9la0xG5

@uCrunch thrust uppercut is your go to ender and kill option because it is a very good followup to dtilt, uptilt, downthrow, and upair

a lot of people are gonna want to DI out when you grab them which also leads to possible deaths from forward throw

@uCrunch side b is a good burst option that also kills at higher percents and also conditions them into shielding. making them shield is a good thing because grab (mostly down throw) is your most consistent kill option at many percents if you have thrust uppercut
